cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is about optical flow estimation using convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning (cs.LG) and the incorporation of feature-driven local convolutions (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of pyramidal feature extraction and feature warping (cs.RO) and the comparison of their results to benchmarks (cs.MM).
